
# 2025-11-21 10:55:15.869224
+Code the following app
+```
+Create a “GemSlide Fusion” Game on the Home Page
+
+Build a puzzle game called GemSlide Fusion, played on a 5×5 grid. Instead of numbers, each tile represents a gem with a color and tier. The player moves tiles using four on-screen arrow buttons (Up, Down, Left, Right), arranged directly below the grid in a typical keyboard arrow-key layout.
+
+Gameplay Mechanics
+
+The game starts with three random gem tiles on the board.
+After every move, one new gem spawns in a random empty tile.
+
+Gems have tiers instead of numbers:
+
+Tier 1 (Common)
+Tier 2 (Uncommon)
+Tier 3 (Rare)
+Tier 4 (Epic)
+Tier 5 (Legendary)
+
+Spawning Rules
+
+New gems spawn with these probabilities:
+
+Tier 1: 70%
+Tier 2: 25%
+Tier 3: 5%
+
+Higher tiers can only be formed through merging.
+
+Movement Rules
+When an arrow is pressed, all gems slide as far as possible in that direction, stopping only when they:
+Hit another gem, or
+Reach the edge of the grid
+If two gems of the same tier collide, they fuse into a single gem of the next tier.
+A fused gem cannot fuse again in the same move, even if another matching gem lands on it.
+
+Special Collision Cases
+
+If three identical gems line up and the player moves toward them:
+Only the two gems farthest in the direction of movement will merge.
+If all five tiles in a row or column contain the same tier, a parallel move merges:
+
+The first two gems,
+
+And the last two gems
+(Resulting in two merged gems plus one leftover in the center.)
+
+Scoring
+
+The score is shown in the upper-right corner.
+
+Score = sum of tier values, where:
+
+Tier 1 = 1 point
+
+Tier 2 = 3 points
+
+Tier 3 = 9 points
+
+Tier 4 = 27 points
+
+Tier 5 = 81 points
+
+Fusing gives bonus points equal to the value of the resulting gem.
+
+Winning Condition
+
+The game is won when a Tier 5 (Legendary Gem) appears anywhere on the board.
+
+Players may continue playing to achieve higher scores.
+
+Game Over Condition
+
+The game ends when:
+
+There are no empty tiles, and
+
+No adjacent tiles have the same tier
+
+When the game ends, the user should be able to share their score.
+
+Placement
+
+Place the GemSlide Fusion game directly on the home page.
+```
+
+Generate an app logo and update the app metadata title and description.

